Have a look at 34137.  I think tht this is a duplicate.

The image in CVS (or the act of getting the image from CVS - not sure which it 
is) seems to be eating a byte from the image.

I had updated a plugin from CVS to test a fix.
Removing the icons that I had retrieved from CVS fixed the problem.

*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of 34137 ***
